class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Total.find?\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Iter</span>.<span class=\"name\">Total</span>.<span class=\"name\">find?</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α </span><span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iterator\">Iterator</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Monadic/Loop.html#Std.IteratorLoop\">IteratorLoop</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iterators.Finite\">Iterators.Finite</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">it</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Total.html#Std.Iter.Total\">Total</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the first output of the iterator for which the predicate `p` returns `true`, or `none` if\nno such output is found.\n\n`O(|it|)`. Short-circuits upon encountering the first match. The elements in `it` are examined in\norder of iteration.\n\nThis variant terminates after finitely many steps and requires a proof that the iterator is\nfinite. If such a proof is not available, consider using `Iter.find?`.\n\nExamples:\n* `[7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.find? (· < 5) = some 1`\n* `[7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.find? (· < 1) = none`\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Total.find?","kind":"def","line":614,"name":"Std.Iter.Total.find?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.lean#L614-L631"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Partial.find?\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Iter</span>.<span class=\"name\">Partial</span>.<span class=\"name\">find?</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α </span><span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iterator\">Iterator</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Monadic/Loop.html#Std.IteratorLoop\">IteratorLoop</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">it</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Partial.html#Std.Iter.Partial\">Partial</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the first output of the iterator for which the predicate `p` returns `true`, or `none` if\nno such output is found.\n\n`O(|it|)`. Short-circuits upon encountering the first match. The elements in `it` are examined in\norder of iteration.\n\nThis function is deprecated. Instead of `it.allowNontermination.find?`, use `it.find?`.\n\nExamples:\n* `[7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.allowNontermination.find? (· < 5) = some 1`\n* `[7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.allowNontermination.find? (· < 1) = none`\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Partial.find?","kind":"def","line":596,"name":"Std.Iter.Partial.find?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.lean#L596-L612"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.find?\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Iter</span>.<span class=\"name\">find?</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α </span><span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iterator\">Iterator</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Monadic/Loop.html#Std.IteratorLoop\">IteratorLoop</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">it</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iter\">Iter</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the first output of the iterator for which the predicate `p` returns `true`, or `none` if\nno such output is found.\n\n`O(|it|)`. Short-circuits upon encountering the first match. The elements in `it` are examined in\norder of iteration.\n\nIf the iterator is not finite, this function might run forever. The variant\n`it.ensureTermination.find?` always terminates after finitely many steps.\n\nExamples:\n* `[7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.find? (· < 5) = some 1`\n* `[7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.find? (· < 1) = none`\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.find?","kind":"def","line":577,"name":"Std.Iter.find?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.lean#L577-L594"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Total.findM?\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Iter</span>.<span class=\"name\">Total</span>.<span class=\"name\">findM?</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α </span><span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w'</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Monad\">Monad</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iterator\">Iterator</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Monadic/Loop.html#Std.IteratorLoop\">IteratorLoop</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iterators.Finite\">Iterators.Finite</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">it</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Total.html#Std.Iter.Total\">Total</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ULift\">ULift</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the first output of the iterator for which the monadic predicate `p` returns `true`, or\n`none` if no such element is found.\n\n`O(|it|)`. Short-circuits when `f` returns `true`. The outputs of `it` are examined in order of\niteration.\n\nThis variant requires terminates after finitely many steps and requires a proof that the iterator is\nfinite. If such a proof is not available, consider using `Iter.findM?`.\n\nExample:\n```lean example\n#eval [7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.findM? fun i => do\n  if i < 5 then\n    return true\n  if i ≤ 6 then\n    IO.println s!\"Almost! {i}\"\n  return false\n```\n```output\nAlmost! 6\nAlmost! 5\n```\n```output\nsome 1\n```\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Total.findM?","kind":"def","line":544,"name":"Std.Iter.Total.findM?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.lean#L544-L575"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Partial.findM?\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Iter</span>.<span class=\"name\">Partial</span>.<span class=\"name\">findM?</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α </span><span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w'</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Monad\">Monad</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iterator\">Iterator</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Monadic/Loop.html#Std.IteratorLoop\">IteratorLoop</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">it</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Partial.html#Std.Iter.Partial\">Partial</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ULift\">ULift</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the first output of the iterator for which the monadic predicate `p` returns `true`, or\n`none` if no such element is found.\n\n`O(|it|)`. Short-circuits when `f` returns `true`. The outputs of `it` are examined in order of\niteration.\n\nThis function is deprecated. Instead of `it.ensureTermination.findM?`, use `it.findM?`.\n\nExample:\n```lean example\n#eval [7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.findM? fun i => do\n  if i < 5 then\n    return true\n  if i ≤ 6 then\n    IO.println s!\"Almost! {i}\"\n  return false\n```\n```output\nAlmost! 6\nAlmost! 5\n```\n```output\nsome 1\n```\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Partial.findM?","kind":"def","line":512,"name":"Std.Iter.Partial.findM?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.lean#L512-L542"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.findM?\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Iter</span>.<span class=\"name\">findM?</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α </span><span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w'</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Monad\">Monad</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iterator\">Iterator</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Monadic/Loop.html#Std.IteratorLoop\">IteratorLoop</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">it</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iter\">Iter</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#ULift\">ULift</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the first output of the iterator for which the monadic predicate `p` returns `true`, or\n`none` if no such element is found.\n\n`O(|it|)`. Short-circuits when `f` returns `true`. The outputs of `it` are examined in order of\niteration.\n\nIf the iterator is not finite, this function might run forever. The variant\n`it.ensureTermination.findM?` always terminates after finitely many steps.\n\nExample:\n```lean example\n#eval [7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.findM? fun i => do\n  if i < 5 then\n    return true\n  if i ≤ 6 then\n    IO.println s!\"Almost! {i}\"\n  return false\n```\n```output\nAlmost! 6\nAlmost! 5\n```\n```output\nsome 1\n```\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.findM?","kind":"def","line":479,"name":"Std.Iter.findM?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.lean#L479-L510"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Total.findSome?\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Iter</span>.<span class=\"name\">Total</span>.<span class=\"name\">findSome?</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α </span><span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">γ</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> x}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iterator\">Iterator</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Monadic/Loop.html#Std.IteratorLoop\">IteratorLoop</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Basic.html#Std.Iterators.Finite\">Iterators.Finite</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Control/Id.html#Id\">Id</a></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">it</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Total.html#Std.Iter.Total\">Total</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">γ</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">γ</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Returns the first non-`none` result of applying `f` to each output of the iterator, in order.\nReturns `none` if `f` returns `none` for all outputs.\n\n`O(|it|)`. Short-circuits when `f` returns `some _`.The outputs of `it` are examined in order of\niteration.\n\nThis variant terminates after finitely many steps and requires a proof that the iterator is\nfinite. If such a proof is not available, consider using `Iter.findSome?`.\n\nExamples:\n * `[7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.ensureTermination.findSome? (fun x => if x < 5 then some (10 * x) else none) = some 10`\n * `[7, 6, 5, 8, 1, 2, 6].iter.ensureTermination.findSome? (fun x => if x < 1 then some (10 * x) else none) = none`\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Total.findSome?","kind":"def","line":459,"name":"Std.Iter.Total.findSome?","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/3b0f2862196c6a8af9eb0025ee650252694013dd/src/Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.lean#L459-L477"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Iterators/Consumers/Loop.html#Std.Iter.Partial.findSome?\"><span class=\"name\">Std</span>.<span class=\"name\">Iter</span>.<span class=\"name\">Partial</span>.<span class=\"name\">findSome?</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α </span><span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w}</span></span>\n</span><spa